<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Pseudotsuga macrocarpa </i>is adapted to long fire-free intervals. Fire kills seeds, seedlings, and most saplings. Most sprouting occurs on trees scorched by surface fire. Mature plants can sprout from the bole and branches after a fire and grow new crowns; however, trees subjected to crown fire rarely sprout. Regeneration in moderately burned stands takes several decades; however, it is less probable after stand-replacing fires because most seed trees are lost, and long distance dispersal is not probable (Howard 1992h, McDonald 1990a).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Long (70-200+ years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
